# shadcn/ui Component Patterns

## Installing shadcn

If shadcn is not yet initialised in the project, run from `frontend/`:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
npx shadcn@latest add <component>
```

Components are generated into `frontend/src/components/ui/`. Never copy-paste component code from the docs manually.

## Adding new components

Always use the CLI — never hand-write shadcn primitives from scratch:

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
npx shadcn@latest add button dialog input

# ❌ BAD – hand-rolling a Button that shadcn already provides
export function Button({ children }) { return <button>{children}</button>; }
```

## Extending components

Customise via `className` + `cn()`. Do **not** edit the generated files in `components/ui/` directly, as they may be regenerated.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD – extend at the call site
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

<Button className={cn("w-full rounded-full", isActive && "bg-primary")} />

// ❌ BAD – modifying components/ui/button.tsx
```

## Prefer shadcn primitives

Use shadcn components for common UI elements before reaching for raw HTML or third-party libraries:

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Clickable action | `Button` |
| Text field | `Input` |
| Overlay | `Dialog` / `Sheet` |
| Dropdown | `DropdownMenu` / `Select` |
| Notification | `Sonner` |
| Loading | `Skeleton` |
